cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a new architecture for multi-task learning of detection and segmentation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the transfer of useful information between single-task CNNs trained on different datasets, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed architecture, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
